@node SCORE "What is the OLFBscore.rexx file?"

  You'll find in this archive, the file OLFBscore.rexx.
  This file is a working example for BBBBS sysops of how
  to utilize Score information sent from Online FootBall.

  The file, as it is, ONLY works for BBBBS sysops, but if
  you have any Arexx knowledge, it should be quite simple
  to edit this file so it can be used on any BBS system.
  If you need help editing it, feel free to call me or any
  of my Beta testers and I'm sure we can get it going.

  What it does:

   At the end of each OLFB game, if the file "OLFBscore.rexx"
  exists in your REXX: dir, the game will send OLFBscore
  information about the just finished game to be used in many
  ways. The information is sent in this format:

OLFBscore.rexx OpponentName GameResult UserName OpponentScore UserScore

  OpponentName = the Name of the player played by the computer.
  GameResult = W if Opponent won, L if Opponent Lost.
  UserName = The name of the BBS caller involved in the game.
  OpponentScore = Final score of the Opponent
  UserScore = Final Score of the User

  OLFBscore can be edited to do many things with this information.
  The file provided will send email to the Opponent telling him
  that he either won or lost at OLFB and show him the final
  score. It will also create a file in the BBS_Text dir that
  will display once per day to each caller showing the latest
  results of OLFB games. A copy of this file will be created
  in the OLFB dir and named "OLFB.sb"

   ** If a file named "OLFB.sb" exists in the OLFB dir,it will
      be displayed at the beginning of each game! **

  Any of the above features can be disabled by the sysop by editing
  the OLFBscore.rexx file as indicated inside the file.

  I put comments in the file to help you understand how it works
  and assist you if you want to adapt it for any other purpose.
  To make it work for other systems than BBBBS, you will need to
  edit the PATHS and make BBS specific adjustments.

@endnode

