@node MORESETUP "Finish setting up OLFB"

  WB 1.3 users! READ THIS > @{"WB 1.3" link WB1.3}

  ALL Systems :

  The @{"OLFB Sysop Challenge" link SYSCHAL} mode allows callers to play head
  head against the sysop!

  @{"OLFBscore.rexx file" LINK SCORE}

  The file "FB.ad" (OLFB$AD.E! for E! systems) is provided so you
  can advertise the game (if ya like). It is an ANSI text file that
  you can install so that it can be viewed during logon, or wherever
  is appropriate for your system.

  If the file "OLFB.announce" exists in your OLFB directory, it's contents
  will be displayed to each player. This is a good place to place messages
  describing new features or challenging players to play against you in
  The Sysop Challenge.

  To Reset the game, use the reset options inside the game at the
  @{"Sysop menu" link SYSFUNC}

  After running the game once, a file will be created named "OLFB.config"
  inside your OLFB directory. If you'd like to have the Plays read directly
  from your Hard drive, rather than from RAM, change line 3 of this file
  to be "0".

  That's it! If you see any bugs, let me know. (I mean it..)
  Matt

  Enjoy.

@endnode

