@node History "OLFB History

 OLFB - History by Matt English

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

  Any Versions not listed here, or bearing any other name other than
  "Matt English" as author are unauthorized copies of this program
  and should be considered as such. As a show of support for people
  who program ORIGINAL Software for the Amiga, please run ONLY
  AUTHORIZED versions of Online FootBall.. Thankyou

  Matt English
  The Alternative BBS
  (503) 761-3043
  14.4, 24 hrs.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

 version 2.0 11-10-94
  > @{"What's new for version 2 ?" link WHATSNEW}

 verions 1.65 thru 1.95
  > Released to BETA Testers only!

 version 1.6 4-23-94
  > OLFB now supports BBBBS, DLG, Cnet & Trinity BBS systems without
    any modifications!! OLFB can also be ran on TransAmiga BBS systems
    with the Startup file provided by Jerry Jordan. Thanks Jerry!!
  > OLFB now reads a "Key" file if one exists, to determine if OLFB
    has been registered or not. This is much more convenient for
    Registered sysops. No longer need to call and Download an entire
    "Registered" archive. Only need to call once to get the keyfile.
  > Animation routines re-written resulting in upto a 300% increase
    in animation speed!
  > No more tied games. A tie at the end of the 4th Quarter will
    go into a Sudden Death overtime period. Play continues until
    either Team scores.
  > Each user now has the option to turn the ball animation off or
    on from the "Options" menu. The preference will be saved in the
    users data file and used each time he plays. This was requested
    by players at 2400 baud. Can really speed up a game!
  > Each player now has the option to adjust their Text Speed for
    OLFB. Text can be displayed VERY fast to VERY slow and every
    speed in between. The preference will be saved in the
    users data file and used each time he plays.
  > Added a Sysop menu for the Sysop to customize and control
    OLFB from inside the game.
  > Users no longer play ONLY against the Amiga! The game will
    choose opponents for new games from ALL the players in the
    Stats Sheets that have played OLFB. The system will pick the
    LEAST active player as the next opponent. This helps eliminate
    all the ZEROS in the stats from players who never finish a
    game. This also acts as an incentive for players to stay ACTIVE!
    Active players will never be chosen as opponents and won't have games
    played for them by the computer. This feature also stops "AMIGA"
    from dominating the Stats Sheets. Sysops can also add ficticious
    Players or Teams from the Sysop menu to enhance game play.
  > Forfeited games now record ALL the stats from the Forfeited game
    rather than just the WIN/LOSS stat.
  > If a text file with the name "OLFB.announce" exists in the OLFB
    directory, it'll be displayed after the intro screen. This is a
    handy way to tell your users about new features or challange them
    to beat you in the stats (:
  > Added penalties. User has the option to accept or decline Penalties
    that do NOT stop play action before the hike.
  > The sysop can now adjust the odds for penalties from the sysop menu!
  > Players returning to OLFB will be shown the current stats of their
    saved game before being asked if they want to continue their saved
    game.
  > An animated Referee has been added!
  > Odds for making a field goal have been adjusted.

 version 1.56 4-2-94
  Released to Registered OLFB sysops only..

 version 1.55 3-25-94
  OLFB now supports BBBBS, DLG & Cnet BBS systems without any
  modifications!! No other BBS game (that I know of) does this!
  The OLFB code has been compiled for much increased access speed!
  This makes the OLFB filesize quite large, however the speed increase
  is well worth the added Disk space. If you like, you can powerpack
  the Online_FootBall file to achieve about a 60% size reduction.
  You now can kick a field goal no matter what Down it is, providing
  you are at the 40 yard line or closer.
  Added HalfTime & game end stats reports.
  Completely Re-programed the logic that the Amiga uses in picking
  his plays. The game is more challenging.
  I made some cosmetic changes & probably a ton of stuff I simply
  can't remember.

  *** Due to some of the logic changes and optimization changes,
      any data files generated from an earlier version of OLFB will
      not be compatable with this version or Future versions. Future
      versions will be backwardly compatable with this version.. ***

 version 1.4 1-16-94
  Couple bugs fixed..
  If a player didn't continue a saved game, he wasn't getting
  credited with a loss in the Stat Sheets like he should have.
  The sort command was getting added to the resident list
  over and over and over.. If you want it resident, set it up
  in your startup-sequence.

 version 1.3 1-10-94
  First major release! ANSI graphics and Stats sheet completed!

 versions 1.0 thru 1.2 were riddled with bugs and spent
 1992 and 1993 in my disk box driving me nuts. (never released)

@endnode

@node RexxPlus "RexxPlus"

 This game is in compiled Arexx. This results in about 2-4 times
 increased execution speed over un-compiled Arexx. It also results
 in a fairly large executable. Since this file is a TRUE executable,
 you may PowerPack it, Implode it, OR make it resident.
 The choice is yours..

 Setting your system up for REXXPLUS is covered in the
 @{"Setup" link SETUP} section.

@endnode

