@node Customize "Customizing OLFB"

                           Customize.OLFB

  Customizing the @{"OLFBscore.rexx file" LINK SCORE}

  You can customize the OLFB play files to have a more local feel,
  or change the odds to make the game easier/harder to play.
  You'll need to be able to use a text editor and learn the following
  formats.. I hope I can explain them good enough..

  The filename of each play file represents what kind of play
  combination has been selected in the game that resulted in this
  file to be called..
  File "12" means offense picked selection 1 and defense selected 2.
  File "34".. Offense 3, defense 4.
  After you've played the game, this will make sense..
  The text of a play should reflect the selected combinations.
  A 3 or 4 offense play, should describe a pass play..

  The first line of each play file has a number.. This number is
  how many plays are in this file. If you ADD new plays to the file,
  increase the number..

  This is an actual play from the game:

111         /* Offense 1, defense 1, play 1 of the file */
1 8 -       /* This play will be 1 thru 8 yards.. The "-" means a loss "+" means gain.*/
The ball is hiked                             Play text
They're going for the Quarterback sneak!          "
The defense reads it well,----                    "
yard loss!!                                       "
END                                     /* Last line */


  The game reads the first line of the file and sees how many plays are in the file.
  It then picks a random play from the file.
  The first line sets a range of yardage that this play will result in
  and weather it's a loss, gain, no gain (0), or Interception or Punt.
  The 2 lines right before "END" will be joined in the program with the
  number of yard gained/lossed spliced in between.

  The easiest thing to do will probably be to look at all the different kinds of
  plays and copy the format.. Be sure to keep a backup of the original plays.
  If you mess up, you could get some funny results..

  If you write a whole bunch of new plays, and wanna send em to me,
  YES! Please do!
  If ya need help, give me a call.

  Matt 503-761-3043

@endnode

@node CLI.FULL "Installing OLFB using CLI MODE"

     TO INSTALL OLFB CLI MODE:    + OLFB v 2.0 +

      First Setup the files as shown > @{"File Setup" link F.SETUP}

      Then call the game from your BBS as follows:

  USAGE: Online_FootBall C Path Timeleft Mins/Secs Name

  "C" tells OLFB that you are running in CLI mode

  "Path" = The Full path of the "OLFB" directory ending in ":" or "/"

  "TimeLeft" = a number that your BBS passes to OLFB telling OLFB
               how much time this player has left for this call.
               This MUST be "0" if your BBS doesn''t pass timeleft.
               You can also pass any number to limit each players time.
                    Example 45 = 45 minutes

  "MINS/SECS" = If timeleft is in minutes, pass "M". If TimeLeft is in
                Seconds, pass S. If timeleft = 0 then pass 0

  "Name" = The name of the caller passed by your BBS.

  Example: Online_FootBall C BBS:Doors/ %tl M %name
  Example: Online_FootBall C Doors: 4500 S Richard Stockton

** You can always see this info by typing "Online_FootBall ?" in a CLI window **

@endnode

@node E.full "Setting up OLFB to run on E!"

   The file setup for OLFB on Excelsior, is identical to the setup
   used for the CLI MODE, EXCEPT for the path of the OLFB directory.
   The OLFB directory MUST exist in your MAIN DOORS PATH.
   Online FootBall will look for the OLFB directory in the directory
   listed in the RESULT CODE returned from the "PATH 6" command.


            Setup the files, then come back here.

                       @{"File Setup" link F.SETUP}


   You now add the game to your BBS menu and call the game
   as an AREXX GAME! Calling the game as DOS Game will not
   work properly for Multi-line systems!

   You need to pass NO parameters to the game.

@endnode

@node 4D.full "Setting up OLFb to run on 4D BBS"

   The file setup for OLFB on 4D BBS, is identical to the setup
   used for the CLI MODE. Setup the files, then come back here.

                        @{"File Setup" link F.SETUP}

   Assuming your path to the OLFB directory is "BBS:Games/"
   then call the game with the following line:

   Online_FootBall 5 BBS:Games/


@endnode

@node F.setup "Setting up The OLFB files for CLI MODE"

     File Setup:

                            ++++++++

      Decide where you are going to put your OLFB directory
      on your system. For this example, I'll use "BBS:Games/"
      but you can substitute any directory you like.

 ++ Excelsior BBS sysops MUST put OLFB dir in your MAIN DOORS dir! ++

                            ++++++++

     1. Copy the file "rexxplslib.library" to your LIBS: directory
     2. Copy the files RPStart & RPStart.info to your
         WBStartup Drawer. (This starts up the RexxPlus
         environment which is needed for this game. Copying
         it to your WBStartup is REQUIRED to run this game!)
         *** WB1.3 users can copy it to C: and run it in your
             startup-sequence.
     3. OPTIONAL - Copy the files RPHi & RPHi.info to your C: directory.
                   This command will stop ALL RexxPlus AND Arexx processes
                   currently running.
     4. Make a directory > "BBS:Games/OLFB"
     5. Make a directory > "BBS:Games/OLFB/Plays"
     6. Copy the file "Online_FootBall" into the "BBS:Games/OLFB" directory.
     7. OPTIONAL - Copy the file "OLFB.announce" to your "BBS:Games/OLFB"
        directory.
     8. Copy these files to "BBS:Games/OLFB/Plays" :
         11
         12
         13
         14
         21
         22
         23
         24
         31
         32
         33
         34
         41
         42
         43
         44
         55
         56
         65
         66
         76
         85
         86
      9. Copy the file "Chal.sound" to your OLFB directory.
     10. Copy the file "C/Sound" to your C: dir. (Should already be there.)
         (Sound was written by @{"Richard Stockton" link RLS} and is provided here
          with his permission. Thanks Richard!)
     11. Copy the file "C/ACCEPTCHAL" to your C: dir.

    **************

    Please consider @{"Registering" link REGISTER} Online FootBall!

    That's it! If you see any bugs, let me know. (I mean it..)
    Matt (503)761-3043

    Enjoy.

@endnode

@node 4D "Setting up OLFb for 4D BBS"

@endnode

@node BBBBS.update "Updating OLFB on BBBBS"

     Attention !!! :
      If you are running any versions of OLFB older than version 1.55
      you will need to do a @{"COMPLETE Installation." link BBBBS.full}

      Future versions will be backwardly compatable to version 1.55.


     TO UPDATE FROM OLFB V 1.55 OR GREATER :

     1. Copy the file "Online_FootBall" over the old one in your
        RexxDoors/data/OLFB directory.
     2. Copy the file "OLFB.announce" to your OLFB directory.
     3. Copy the file "Chal.sound" to your OLFB directory.
     4. Copy the file "C/Sound" to your C: dir. (Should already be there.)
        (Sound was written by @{"Richard Stockton" link RLS} and is provided here
         with his permission. Thanks Richard!)
     5. Copy the file "C/ACCEPTCHAL" to your C: dir.

@endnode

