@node CNet.Update "Updating OLFB on CNET"   + OLFB v 2.0 +

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

     Attention !!! :
      If you are running any versions of OLFB older than version 1.55
      you will need to delete all the files in your OLFB directory
      and do a @{"Complete Installation" link CNET.FULL}

      The files generated by this version of OLFB are NOT compatable
      with versions older than ver 1.55!
      Future versions will be backwardly compatable to version 1.55.

     Also, if you are running un-authorized versions of OLFB claiming to
     have been written by anyone other than Matt English, the data files
     WILL NOT be compatable with data files used by authentic
     releases of OLFB. You should either rename your old OLFB
     directory or delete it's contents to avoid conflicts.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

     The easiest thing to do is de-compress this archive to RAM:
     and then run the AREXX script "CNetFB.Install"
     "CNetFB.Install" will BOTH install or upgrade OLFB v 1.55 and greater.
     Then, Adopt Online FootBall as a SINGLE USER Pfile.
     "CNetFB.Install" provided by Trebor of Asgard BBS! Thanks Trebor!


     Updating Manually

     1. Copy the file "Online_FootBall" over the old one in your
        PFiles: directory.
     2. Copy the file "OLFB.announce" to your Pfiles:OLFB directory.
     3. Copy the file "Chal.sound" to your Pfiles:OLFB directory.
     4. Copy the file "C/Sound" to your C: dir.
        (Sound was written by @{"Richard Stockton" link RLS} and is provided here
         with his permission. Thanks Richard!)
     5. Copy the file "C/ACCEPTCHAL" to your C: dir.

    Please consider @{"registering" link REGISTER} Online_FootBall.

@endnode

@node CNet.full "Complete Installation for CNET"

     TO Install OLFB ON CNET:    + OLFB v 2.0 +

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

     Attention !!! :
      If you are running any versions of OLFB older than version 1.55
      you will need to delete all the files in your OLFB directory
      before installing this version.

      The files generated by this version of OLFB are NOT compatable
      with versions older than ver 1.55!
      Future versions will be backwardly compatable to version 1.55.

     Also, if you are running un-authorized versions of OLFB claiming to
     have been written by anyone other than Matt English, the data files
     WILL NOT be compatable with data files used by authentic
     releases of OLFB. You should either rename your old OLFB
     directory or delete it's contents to avoid conflicts.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

     The easiest thing to do is de-compress this archive to RAM:
     and then run the AREXX script "CNetFB.Install"
     "CNetFB.Install" will BOTH install or upgrade OLFB v 1.55 and greater.
     Then, Adopt Online FootBall as a SINGLE USER Pfile.
     "CNetFB.Install" provided by Trebor of Asgard BBS! Thanks Trebor!

     MANUAL INSTALLATION :

     1. Copy the file "rexxplslib.library" to your LIBS: directory
     2. Copy the files RPStart & RPStart.info to your
         WBStartup Drawer. (This starts up the RexxPlus
         environment which is needed for this game. Copying
         it to you WBStartup is REQUIRED to run this game!)
         ** WB1.3 users can copy it to C: and run it in your
            startup-sequence.
     3. Copy the files RPHi & RPHi.info to your C: directory.
         This command will stop ALL RexxPlus AND Arexx processes
         currently running.
     4. Copy the file "Online_Football" to your PFiles: directory.
     5. Make a directory > "Pfiles:OLFB"
     6. Make a directory > "PFiles:OLFB/Plays"
     7. Copy these files to "Pfiles:OLFB/Plays" :
         11
         12
         13
         14
         21
         22
         23
         24
         31
         32
         33
         34
         41
         42
         43
         44
         55
         56
         65
         66
         76
         85
         86
     8. OPTIONAL - Copy the file "OLFB.announce" to your "PFiles:OLFB"
        directory. Any file named "OLFB.announce" will be displayed
        each time the game is played.
     9. Copy the file "Chal.sound" to your Pfiles:OLFB directory.
     10. Copy the file "C/Sound" to your C: dir.
        (Sound was written by @{"Richard Stockton" link RLS} and is provided here
         with his permission. Thanks Richard!)
     11. Copy the file "C/ACCEPTCHAL" to your C: dir.

     12. Adopt Online FootBall as a SINGLE USER Pfile.


    Please consider @{"Registering" link REGISTER} Online FootBall!

    That's it! If you see any bugs, let me know. (I mean it..)
    Matt (503)761-3043

    Enjoy.

@endnode

